laboratory_examinations.findings: DMB ratio was 33.68 mg/mmol creatinine (normal range for 2–17 y/o: <20.98).

DS at 3.33 µg/mmol creatinine (normal range: <1.56), HS at 1.41 µg/mmol creatinine (normal range: <3.10), KS at 12.97 µg/mmol creatinine (normal range: <13.79), and CS at 8.72 µg/mmol creatinine (normal range: <59.66).
All normal for MPS I, MPS II, MPS IIIB, MPS IVA, and MPS VI.
Revealed a heterozygous genetic variant c.104C > A in the GUSB gene (pathogenic) and c.1454C > T in the GUSB gene (likely pathogenic).
